One cultural development is no one really makes fun of fashion shows anymore. Back in the day a huge part of normie humor was making fun of those designer clothes models wear on the walkway and saying regular ppl dress better, but now everyone knows it's like an abstract art form

Like in 2015 people would post a picture of some Zoglenciaga model wearing some large moon-shaped object and say "wtf is this lol no thanks I prefer jeans and a white shirt" but now they know it's supposed to be like a theatrical and impractical "surrealist object" and accept it.
